11:21.960 --> 11:27.960
Jupiter, being larger and more serious, receives many more blows, many more.

11:27.960 --> 11:33.960
In 1994, the comet Shoemaker-Levy 9 hit Jupiter.

11:33.960 --> 11:39.960
The fierce gravitational waves of Jupiter had torn the comet into dozens of pieces,

11:39.960 --> 11:43.960
and each one of them crashed against the planet, one after the other,

11:43.960 --> 11:46.960
with the force of millions of nuclear weapons.

11:46.960 --> 11:50.960
The scars left in the upper atmosphere lasted for months.

11:50.960 --> 11:53.960
Many have been seen in the atmosphere of Jupiter,

11:53.960 --> 11:59.960
